  <title translate="true">Cross Sectional Model: Specified Heads</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">Cross Sectional Model: Specified Heads</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Create a point object </text><image src="CreatePoint.png" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Normal"><title translate="true">Create Point Object button</title></image><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> in the bottom most layer of the first column (circled in red in the figure below).</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="text-align:center;"><image src="CrossSection10.bmp" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption"></image></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">In the Object Properties dialog box, go to the MODFLOW Features tab and check the checkbox for the CHD package. &#160;Set the starting and ending times to -1 and 0 respectively. Set both the starting and ending heads to 55. &#160;Repeat the process for the uppermost cell in the last column on the right except set the heads to 50.</text></para>
